				<td colspan="2"><span>The general AAs aren't too shabby.
<br />

<br />
The class specific AAs pretty much blow.
<br />

<br />
I'm still on the &quot;not buying OoW&quot; wagon until they fix other game-wide issues such as the raider vs non-raider thing.
<br />

<br />
Couple of specific thoughts:
<br />

<br />
AE Rampage:  Someone else said it best when they said break all the mez'es while doing insignificant melee damage.  This wouldn't ever be used unless farming greens for tradeskill and/or faction.
<br />

<br />
Bellow:  Its a pulling tool.  More damage is insignficant.  With an 18 second recycle time it isn't even usefull for interupting casting when I need it.  I still have to have mez loaded to interupt casting with any ounce of consistency.
<br />

<br />
Taunt:  I still don't think we need it, but if you are going to give it to us, make it useable.  Again, someone else said it best when they said 100% more of 0 is still 0.
<br />

<br />
The illusiong thing is kindof snazzy, but its a toy, not something really usefull.
<br />

<br />
Making the epic break the cap is a very bad idea for the reason stated above about being tied to a single piece of gear.  The difference between the raiders and non-raiders is big enough as it is.  We don't need to inflate it even more by somthing like that.  I'm hoping that since there aren't any AA to increase the cap that they are removing the cap.
<br />

<br />
